  <span id="freeText6547943498296898862" style="display:none"><strong>Discovering Music’s Depth and Power . . .</strong><br /><br />In “Musicophilia: Tales of Music and the Brain,” neurologist Oliver Sacks demonstrated the healing power of music. Through a series of fascinating narratives, the author--dubbed “poet laureate of medicine” by The New York Times--explored a variety of unique musical phenomena. Sharing observations and insights, Sachs revealed the nature of music and the roles music plays in the lives of individuals struggling with medical, psychological, and social issues. Delving into diverse case histories, the author told moving stories of how music helped and healed people with amnesia and aphasia, anxiety and depression, disease and dementia, seizures and strokes, in dramatic and unexpected ways.</span>
